==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[absorptio]]'', from ''[[absorbere]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-absorption.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act or process of [[absorbing]] or [[sucking]] in anything, or of being [[absorbed]] and made to [[disappear]]; as, the ''absorption'' of bodies in a [[whirlpool]], the ''absorption'' of a smaller tribe into a larger.
# {{context|chemistry|physics}} An [[imbibing]] or [[reception]] by [[molecular]] or chemical action; as, the ''absorption'' of light, heat, electricity, etc.
# {{physiology}} In living organisms, the process by which the materials of growth and [[nutrition]] are absorbed and conveyed to the [[tissue]]s and [[organ]]s.
# Entire [[engrossment]] or occupation of the mind; as, ''absorption'' in some employment.

